Usage: gitnexus group [options] [command]

Manage repository groups for cross-index impact analysis

Options:
  -h, --help                              display help for command

Commands:
  create [options] <name>                 Create a new group with template group.yaml
  add <group> <groupPath> <registryName>  Add a repo to a group. <groupPath> = hierarchy path (e.g. hr/hiring/backend), <registryName> = name from registry
  remove <group> <path>                   Remove a repo from a group
  list [name]                             List all groups or details of one
  status <name>                           Check staleness of group and repos
  sync [options] <name>                   Sync Contract Registry — extract contracts and build cross-links
  query [options] <name> <query>          Search execution flows across all repos in a group
  contracts [options] <name>              Inspect Contract Registry
  help [command]                          display help for command
No groups configured. Create one with: gitnexus group create <name>
